Copper in London Declines for Fourth Straight Day on China Demand Concerns

-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 
2011-04-14T00:06:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/copper-in-london-declines-for-fourth-straight-day-on-china-demand-concerns.html
Copper in  London  declined for a
fourth day, the longest period of decline since January, as
investors retreated on concern  China  may step up its credit
tightening measures to cool asset prices.  The metal for three-month delivery on the London Metal
Exchange fell as much as 0.6 percent to $9,449.75 a metric ton,
and trade at $9,450 by 8:05 a.m. in  Singapore . It dropped to a
one-week low of $9,443 a ton yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net  